Zimbabwe’s former president Robert Mugabe remains hospitalised in Singapore. His successor President Emmerson Mnangagwa says Mugabe has been receiving medical care there for four months. Ninety five-year-old Mugabe’s ailment has not been disclosed but Mnangagwa says he’s responding well to treatment. In November last year Mnangagwa announced that the former president unable to walk because of ill health and old age. WATCH BELOW: 